quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  6,60,"It is He Who takes your souls by night, and has knowledge of all that you have done by day. And by day, He raises you up again, that a term appointed is fulfilled. In the end, to Him will be your return, and then will He show you the truth of all that you did"
  6,61,"He is the Irresistible, high above His worshippers, and He sets guardians over you. Then when death approaches one of you, Our angels take her soul, and they never fail in their duty"
  6,62,"Then they are returned to God, their Protector, the Reality. Is not His the command? And He is the swiftest in taking account"
  6,63,"Say, “Who is it that delivers you from the dark recesses of land and sea, when you call upon Him in humility and with fear, ‘If He would only deliver us from this, then we will truly show our gratitude.’ ”"
  6,64,"Say, “It is God that delivers you from these and all other distresses, yet you worship false gods.”"
  6,65,"Say, “He has power to send calamities on you, from above and below. Or to cover you with confusion and strife, giving you a taste of mutual vengeance, each from the other.” See how We explain the signs, that they may understand"
  6,66,"But your people reject this, though it is the truth. Say, “I do not have the responsibility for arranging your affairs"
  6,67,"“For every message is a limit of time, and soon will you know it.”"
  6,68,"When you see people engaged in vain talk about Our signs, ignore them until they talk of something different. If Satan makes you forget, then after remembering, do not sit in the company of those who do wrong"